<div id="review_2569345616" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2569345616" />
    <a title="Lata" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13126933-lata"><img alt="Lata" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1525485137p2/13126933.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2569345616?book_show_action=true">Dec 11, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lata" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lata" href="/user/show/13126933-lata">Lata</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9780061738562" href="/book/show/8519696-the-adventure-of-the-christmas-pudding">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13126933-lata?shelf=classic">classic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13126933-lata?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13126933-lata?shelf=x2018-read">x2018-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13126933-lata?shelf=auth-f">auth-f</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2569345616" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16773683215641009973">A really enjoyable collection of short stories. <br/>-<i>The Adventure of the Christmas Pudding (a.k.a The Theft of the Royal Ruby)</i>: <b> 4.5 stars</b>. I loved how Poirot chatted with the lady of the house, and how he got along with the kids. I liked how this relationship helped him flush out the murderer.<br/>-<i>The Mystery of the Spanish Chest</i>: <b>4.5 stars</b>. As soon as Poirot examined the chest, I had to throw out my assumptions. I didn&apos;t figure out the murderer, but I enjoyed watching Poirot work in this story.<br/>-<i>The U</i></span>
  <span id="freeText16773683215641009973" style="display:none">A really enjoyable collection of short stories. <br />-<i>The Adventure of the Christmas Pudding (a.k.a The Theft of the Royal Ruby)</i>: <b> 4.5 stars</b>. I loved how Poirot chatted with the lady of the house, and how he got along with the kids. I liked how this relationship helped him flush out the murderer.<br />-<i>The Mystery of the Spanish Chest</i>: <b>4.5 stars</b>. As soon as Poirot examined the chest, I had to throw out my assumptions. I didn't figure out the murderer, but I enjoyed watching Poirot work in this story.<br />-<i>The Under Dog</i>: <b>4 stars</b>. Poirot puts on quite the comedy act (behaving like the detectives he gently chides for not using their brains) in an effort to freak out a murderer.<br />-<i>Four and Twenty Blackbirds</i>: <b>3 stars</b>. Figured this one out really easily because of the unusual eating choices at the restaurant.<br />-<i>The Dream</i>: <b>3 stars</b>. A really short mystery that didn't really work for me.<br />-<i>Greenshaw's Folly</i>: <b>3.5 stars</b>. Though Jane doesn't appear for much of the story, she astutely surmised what had happened in the case (I figured out the murder.) It was neat finally meeting Jane's nephew, whom she has mentioned in other stories.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16773683215641009973" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


