              <span id="reviewTextContainer2202690525" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10600656207833118090">A really enjoyable collection of short stories!<br/><br/>I&apos;m not the biggest fan of these types of collections, especially murder mysteries as I like the stories to slowly reveal the clues. I also tend to find that most have one or two weaker tales, but I didn&apos;t find that with this collection.<br/>There&apos;s 6 in total, 5 of them including Poirot and the last featuring Miss Marple.<br/><br/>The titular story &apos;The Adventure of the Christmas Pudding&apos; was my favorite, especially at this festive time of year. <br/>The Mystery of th</span>
  <span id="freeText10600656207833118090" style="display:none">A really enjoyable collection of short stories!<br /><br />I'm not the biggest fan of these types of collections, especially murder mysteries as I like the stories to slowly reveal the clues. I also tend to find that most have one or two weaker tales, but I didn't find that with this collection.<br />There's 6 in total, 5 of them including Poirot and the last featuring Miss Marple.<br /><br />The titular story 'The Adventure of the Christmas Pudding' was my favorite, especially at this festive time of year. <br />The Mystery of the Spanish Chest and The Dream are good too!<br />The remaining three The Under Dog, Four-and-Twenty Blackbirds and Greenshaw's Folly are all worthy additions.<br /><br />This is the third short story collection I've come across as I'm working my way through all the Poirot's, I've enjoyed this one more than <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/477597.Poirot_Investigates" title="Poirot Investigates by Agatha Christie" rel="nofollow noopener">Poirot Investigates</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/982149.Murder_in_the_Mews__Hercule_Poirot___18_" title="Murder in the Mews (Hercule Poirot, #18) by Agatha Christie" rel="nofollow noopener">Murder in the Mews</a>.</span>
