<div id="review_2620643311" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2620643311" />
    <a title="AnnaG" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/62187194-annag"><img alt="AnnaG" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1483315359p2/62187194.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2620643311?book_show_action=true">Dec 29, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="AnnaG" class="user" itemprop="url" name="AnnaG" href="/user/show/62187194-annag">AnnaG</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780008164980" href="/book/show/31134108-the-adventure-of-the-christmas-pudding">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/62187194-annag?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/62187194-annag?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/62187194-annag?shelf=glamour">glamour</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2620643311" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3236637771692695943">This set of short stories feels like a set of ideas that Agatha Christie had for books that she didn&apos;t have time to write. Any and all of them could have been cracking books in their own right, but within the limitations of a short story you don&apos;t get the suspense and build up that you expect from a Christie.</span>
  <span id="freeText3236637771692695943" style="display:none">This set of short stories feels like a set of ideas that Agatha Christie had for books that she didn't have time to write. Any and all of them could have been cracking books in their own right, but within the limitations of a short story you don't get the suspense and build up that you expect from a Christie.</span>
